  <brief_title>Study to Detect Hypotensive Episodes During Spinal Anesthesia for Cesarean Section Using a Noninvasive Continuous Device</brief_title>
  <official_title>Hypotensive Episodes During Cesarean Section Detected by a Continuous Non-invasive Arterial Pressure Measurement Device Are Missed by the Oscillometric Blood Pressure Measurement</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University of Schleswig-Holstein</agency>
