  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypotension after spinal anesthesia for Cesarean section occurs in up to 90% usually under
      five minutes after local anesthetics administration. These changes are poorly depicted by
      oscillometric measurements. The investigators hypothesized, that a continuous noninvasive
      device detects more hypotensive periods with lower blood pressures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
